2026-04-30T08:48:57.6039602Z           "commits": [
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6040189Z             {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6040495Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6041106Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6041622Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6042039Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6042443Z               },
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6042769Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6043174Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6043640Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6043970Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6060094Z               },
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6060456Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6060949Z               "id": "6a3b753c4fc2941d1636d6a47de580edd778cc9c",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6069131Z               "message": "Add toggles to skip SMTP/HTTP/DNSBL checks in restricted networks\n\nIntroduces three default-on options on ValidationOptions\n(EnableSmtpProbes, EnableHttpProbes, EnableDnsbl) so users in\nenvironments where outbound port 25, HTTPS, or public DNSBL queries\nare blocked can disable those check categories without code changes.\n\nCLI flags (opt-out, mirroring --mask-trace / --no-mask-trace):\n  --no-smtp        skip SMTP probes (port 25 / 465 / 587)\n  --no-http        skip MTA-STS, security.txt, BIMI, crt.sh\n  --no-dnsbl       skip Spamhaus / Barracuda / SpamCop / RHSBL\n  --restricted-network  preset for all three\n\nWeb UI: new \"Validation options\" panel with three checkboxes plus a\ntext input for additional DKIM selectors. Choices persist client-side\nvia localStorage. Operators can also pin instance-wide defaults via\nEnableSmtpProbes / EnableHttpProbes / EnableDnsbl env vars; server\ndefaults AND with request values, so an admin-disabled category can\nnever be re-enabled by clients.\n\nDisabled checks emit one Info-severity result naming the flag, matching\nthe existing OpenRelayCheck / CatchAllDetectionCheck skip pattern.\nSMTP and HTTP prefetch in DomainValidator are also gated to avoid\nfiring probes that no check will consume.",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6077547Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T08:24:38Z",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6078210Z               "tree_id": "6fd4a4944bfaa248377cffd554433f79d07f5069",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6079420Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/6a3b753c4fc2941d1636d6a47de580edd778cc9c"
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6080130Z             },
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6080394Z             {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6080692Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6081080Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6081652Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6081939Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6082205Z               },
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6082400Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6082688Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6082977Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6083211Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6083430Z               },
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6083610Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6083871Z               "id": "831146a415b30b1fcebc43a912962e48d35431f1",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6091658Z               "message": "Show full DKIM selector list in web UI; expose options on GET API\n\nWeb UI changes:\n- Validation options panel is no longer collapsible — always visible.\n- DKIM field renamed to \"DKIM selectors\" and pre-filled with the\n  built-in default list (fetched from new /api/defaults endpoint).\n  Server semantics already replace defaults with the request list when\n  set (DkimChecks.cs); this just makes that visible and editable.\n- localStorage key for selectors is `dkimSelectors` (no longer\n  `additionalDkimSelectors`) to reflect the full-list semantics.\n\nAPI surface:\n- New GET /api/defaults returns { dkimSelectors: [...] } so the UI can\n  pre-fill without duplicating the server's built-in list.\n- GET /api/validate/{domain} now accepts query parameters mirroring\n  the CLI flags: noSmtp, noHttp, noDnsbl, restricted, dkimSelectors,\n  axfr, catchAll, openRelay, openResolver, privateDnsbl. Previously\n  this convenience endpoint ignored client preferences entirely.\n  Same AND-logic with server defaults as POST: admin-disabled\n  categories cannot be re-enabled by callers.\n- DkimSelectorsCheck.CommonSelectors made public so the Web project\n  can reference it from /api/defaults without duplication.",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6096588Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T08:31:35Z",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6096917Z               "tree_id": "6dd3d2407e7012c8e445e061f42e80e6d24be578",
2026-04-30T08:48:57.6097397Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/831146a415b30b1fcebc43a912962e48d35431f1"
